[{"text": "One thing the world needs,", "start": 17.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one thing this country desperately needs", "start": 19.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a better way", "start": 21.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of conducting our political debates.", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We need to rediscover", "start": 25.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the lost art of democratic argument.", "start": 27.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 30.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "If you think about the arguments we have,", "start": 36.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "most of the time it's shouting matches", "start": 39.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on cable television,", "start": 41.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "ideological food fights on the floor of Congress.", "start": 43.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I have a suggestion.", "start": 48.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Look at all the arguments we have these days", "start": 50.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over health care,", "start": 53.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "over bonuses and bailouts on Wall Street,", "start": 55.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over the gap between rich and poor,", "start": 58.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over affirmative action and same-sex marriage.", "start": 61.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Lying just beneath the surface", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of those arguments,", "start": 66.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with passions raging on all sides,", "start": 69.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are big questions", "start": 72.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of moral philosophy,", "start": 75.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "big questions of justice.", "start": 77.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But we too rarely", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "articulate and defend", "start": 81.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and argue about", "start": 84.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "those big moral questions in our politics.", "start": 86.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what I would like to do today", "start": 89.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is have something of a discussion.", "start": 92.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "First, let me take", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a famous philosopher", "start": 96.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who wrote about those questions", "start": 98.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of justice and morality,", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "give you a very short lecture", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on Aristotle of ancient Athens,", "start": 104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Aristotle's theory of justice,", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then have a discussion here", "start": 109.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to see whether Aristotle's ideas", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "actually inform", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the way we think and argue", "start": 116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about questions today.", "start": 118.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, are you ready for the lecture?", "start": 121.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "According to Aristotle,", "start": 125.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "justice means giving people what they deserve.", "start": 127.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's it; that's the lecture.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 135.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, you may say, well, that's obvious enough.", "start": 138.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The real questions begin", "start": 140.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when it comes to arguing about", "start": 142.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who deserves what and why.", "start": 144.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Take the example of flutes.", "start": 148.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Suppose we're distributing flutes.", "start": 150.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Who should get the best ones?", "start": 153.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's see what people --", "start": 155.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What would you say?", "start": 157.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Who should get the best flute?", "start": 159.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You can just call it out.", "start": 161.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Audience: Random.)", "start": 163.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Michael Sandel: At random. You would do it by lottery.", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Or by the first person to rush into the hall to get them.", "start": 167.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Who else?", "start": 171.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Audience: The best flute players.)", "start": 173.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: The best flute players. (Audience: The worst flute players.)", "start": 175.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: The worst flute players.", "start": 177.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "How many say the best flute players?", "start": 180.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why?", "start": 184.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Actually, that was Aristotle's answer too.", "start": 187.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 190.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But here's a harder question.", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why do you think,", "start": 194.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "those of you who voted this way,", "start": 196.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the best flutes should go to the best flute players?", "start": 198.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Peter: The greatest benefit to all.", "start": 201.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: The greatest benefit to all.", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We'll hear better music", "start": 205.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if the best flutes should go to the best flute players.", "start": 207.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's Peter? (Audience: Peter.)", "start": 210.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: All right.", "start": 212.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Well, it's a good reason.", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We'll all be better off if good music is played", "start": 217.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rather than terrible music.", "start": 219.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But Peter,", "start": 223.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Aristotle doesn't agree with you that that's the reason.", "start": 225.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's all right.", "start": 228.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Aristotle had a different reason", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for saying the best flutes should go to the best flute players.", "start": 232.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He said,", "start": 235.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's what flutes are for --", "start": 237.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be played well.", "start": 239.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He says that to reason about", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "just distribution of a thing,", "start": 244.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we have to reason about,", "start": 247.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and sometimes argue about,", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the purpose of the thing,", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or the social activity --", "start": 254.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in this case, musical performance.", "start": 256.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the point, the essential nature,", "start": 258.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of musical performance", "start": 260.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is to produce excellent music.", "start": 262.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It'll be a happy byproduct", "start": 264.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that we'll all benefit.", "start": 266.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But when we think about justice,", "start": 270.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Aristotle says,", "start": 273.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what we really need to think about", "start": 275.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the essential nature of the activity in question", "start": 277.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the qualities that are worth", "start": 281.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "honoring and admiring and recognizing.", "start": 284.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One of the reasons", "start": 287.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the best flute players should get the best flutes", "start": 289.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that musical performance", "start": 291.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not only to make the rest of us happy,", "start": 293.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but to honor", "start": 295.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and recognize", "start": 297.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the excellence", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the best musicians.", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, flutes may seem ... the distribution of flutes", "start": 303.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "may seem a trivial case.", "start": 306.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let's take a contemporary example", "start": 309.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the dispute about justice.", "start": 311.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It had to do with golf.", "start": 314.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Casey Martin -- a few years ago,", "start": 316.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Casey Martin --", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "did any of you hear about him?", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He was a very good golfer,", "start": 322.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but he had a disability.", "start": 324.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He had a bad leg, a circulatory problem,", "start": 326.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that made it very painful", "start": 329.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for him to walk the course.", "start": 331.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In fact, it carried risk of injury.", "start": 334.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He asked the PGA,", "start": 338.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Professional Golfers' Association,", "start": 340.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for permission to use a golf cart", "start": 342.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the PGA tournaments.", "start": 345.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They said, \"No.", "start": 347.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now that would give you an unfair advantage.\"", "start": 349.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He sued,", "start": 351.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and his case went all the way", "start": 353.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the Supreme Court, believe it or not,", "start": 355.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the case over the golf cart,", "start": 357.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because the law says", "start": 360.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the disabled", "start": 362.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "must be accommodated,", "start": 364.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "provided the accommodation does not", "start": 367.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "change the essential nature", "start": 370.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the activity.", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He says, \"I'm a great golfer.", "start": 375.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I want to compete.", "start": 377.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But I need a golf cart", "start": 379.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to get from one hole to the next.\"", "start": 381.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Suppose you were", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on the Supreme Court.", "start": 385.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Suppose you were deciding", "start": 387.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the justice of this case.", "start": 389.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "How many here would say", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that Casey Martin does have a right to use a golf cart?", "start": 394.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And how many say, no, he doesn't?", "start": 397.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "All right, let's take a poll, show of hands.", "start": 401.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How many would rule in favor of Casey Martin?", "start": 403.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And how many would not? How many would say he doesn't?", "start": 407.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "All right, we have a good division of opinion here.", "start": 410.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Someone who would not", "start": 414.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "grant Casey Martin the right to a golf cart,", "start": 416.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what would be your reason?", "start": 418.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Raise your hand, and we'll try to get you a microphone.", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What would be your reason?", "start": 422.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Audience: It'd be an unfair advantage.)", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: It would be an unfair advantage", "start": 427.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if he gets to ride in a golf cart.", "start": 430.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "All right, those of you,", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I imagine most of you who would not give him the golf cart", "start": 434.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "worry about an unfair advantage.", "start": 437.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What about those of you who say", "start": 439.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he should be given a golf cart?", "start": 441.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How would you answer the objection?", "start": 443.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yes, all right.", "start": 445.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Audience: The cart's not part of the game.", "start": 447.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: What's your name? (Audience: Charlie.)", "start": 450.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: Charlie says --", "start": 453.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We'll get Charlie a microphone in case someone wants to reply.", "start": 456.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Tell us, Charlie,", "start": 458.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why would you say he should be able to use a golf cart?", "start": 460.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Charlie: The cart's not part of the game.", "start": 463.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: But what about walking from hole to hole?", "start": 467.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Charlie: It doesn't matter; it's not part of the game.", "start": 470.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: Walking the course is not part of the game of golf?", "start": 473.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Charlie: Not in my book, it isn't.", "start": 477.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: All right. Stay there, Charlie.", "start": 479.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 481.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Who has an answer for Charlie?", "start": 483.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "All right, who has an answer for Charlie?", "start": 486.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What would you say?", "start": 488.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Audience: The endurance element is a very important part of the game,", "start": 490.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "walking all those holes.", "start": 493.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: Walking all those holes?", "start": 495.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's part of the game of golf? (Audience: Absolutely.)", "start": 497.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: What's your name? (Audience: Warren.)", "start": 500.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "MS: Warren.", "start": 502.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Charlie, what do you say to Warren?", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Charley: I'll stick to my original thesis.", "start": 509.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 511.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "MS: Warren, are you a golfer?", "start": 517.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Warren: I am not a golfer.", "start": 519.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Charley: And I am. (MS: Okay.)", "start": 521.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 523.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 525.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "You know,", "start": 529.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's interesting.", "start": 531.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In the case, in the lower court,", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they brought in golfing greats", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to testify on this very issue.", "start": 540.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Is walking the course essential to the game?", "start": 544.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they brought in Jack Nicklaus and Arnold Palmer.", "start": 547.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And what do you suppose they all said?", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yes. They agreed with Warren.", "start": 552.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They said, yes, walking the course", "start": 555.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is strenuous physical exercise.", "start": 557.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The fatigue factor is an important part of golf.", "start": 559.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And so it would change", "start": 562.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the fundamental nature of the game", "start": 564.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to give him the golf cart.", "start": 567.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, notice,", "start": 569.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "something interesting --", "start": 571.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Well, I should tell you about the Supreme Court first.", "start": 573.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Supreme Court", "start": 575.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "decided.", "start": 577.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What do you suppose they said?", "start": 579.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They said yes,", "start": 582.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that Casey Martin must be provided a golf cart.", "start": 584.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Seven to two, they ruled.", "start": 587.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What was interesting about their ruling", "start": 590.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and about the discussion we've just had", "start": 594.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that the discussion about", "start": 598.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the right, the justice, of the matter", "start": 600.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "depended on", "start": 602.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "figuring out what is", "start": 604.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the essential nature of golf.", "start": 607.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the Supreme Court justices", "start": 610.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "wrestled with that question.", "start": 612.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And Justice Stevens, writing for the majority,", "start": 614.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "said he had read all about the history of golf,", "start": 616.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the essential point of the game", "start": 621.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is to get very small ball from one place", "start": 624.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into a hole", "start": 626.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in as few strokes as possible,", "start": 628.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and that walking was not essential, but incidental.", "start": 631.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, there were two dissenters,", "start": 633.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one of whom was Justice Scalia.", "start": 635.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He wouldn't have granted the cart,", "start": 640.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and he had a very interesting dissent.", "start": 643.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's interesting because", "start": 645.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he rejected the Aristotelian premise", "start": 647.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "underlying the majority's opinion.", "start": 650.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said it's not possible", "start": 652.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to determine the essential nature", "start": 655.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of a game like golf.", "start": 658.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Here's how he put it.", "start": 660.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"To say that something is essential", "start": 662.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is ordinarily to say that it is necessary", "start": 664.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the achievement of a certain object.", "start": 666.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But since it is the very nature of a game", "start": 669.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to have no object except amusement,", "start": 671.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 675.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "that is, what distinguishes games", "start": 679.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from productive activity,", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 683.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it is quite impossible to say", "start": 686.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that any of a game's arbitrary rules", "start": 688.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is essential.\"", "start": 691.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So there you have Justice Scalia", "start": 693.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "taking on the Aristotelian premise", "start": 695.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the majority's opinion.", "start": 698.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Justice Scalia's opinion", "start": 701.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is questionable", "start": 704.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for two reasons.", "start": 706.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "First, no real sports fan would talk that way.", "start": 708.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 711.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If we had thought that the rules", "start": 713.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the sports we care about", "start": 715.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are merely arbitrary,", "start": 717.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rather than designed to call forth", "start": 719.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the virtues and the excellences", "start": 722.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that we think are worthy of admiring,", "start": 725.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we wouldn't care about the outcome of the game.", "start": 727.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's also objectionable", "start": 730.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on a second ground.", "start": 733.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "On the face of it,", "start": 735.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it seemed to be -- this debate about the golf cart --", "start": 737.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "an argument about fairness,", "start": 740.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what's an unfair advantage.", "start": 743.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But if fairness were the only thing at stake,", "start": 747.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "there would have been an easy and obvious solution.", "start": 750.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What would it be? (Audience: Let everyone use the cart.)", "start": 753.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let everyone ride in a golf cart", "start": 755.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if they want to.", "start": 758.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Then the fairness objection goes away.", "start": 760.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But letting everyone ride in a cart", "start": 763.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "would have been, I suspect,", "start": 766.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "more anathema", "start": 768.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the golfing greats", "start": 770.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to the PGA,", "start": 772.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "even than making an exception for Casey Martin.", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why?", "start": 776.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because what was at stake", "start": 778.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the dispute over the golf cart", "start": 780.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was not only the essential nature of golf,", "start": 783.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but, relatedly, the question:", "start": 786.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What abilities", "start": 789.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are worthy", "start": 792.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of honor and recognition", "start": 794.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as athletic talents?", "start": 796.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let me put the point", "start": 799.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as delicately as possible:", "start": 801.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Golfers are a little sensitive", "start": 804.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the athletic status of their game.", "start": 806.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 809.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "After all, there's no running or jumping,", "start": 815.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the ball stands still.", "start": 818.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 821.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So if golfing is the kind of game", "start": 824.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that can be played while riding around in a golf cart,", "start": 827.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it would be hard to confer", "start": 830.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on the golfing greats", "start": 833.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the status that we confer,", "start": 835.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the honor and recognition", "start": 837.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that goes to truly great athletes.", "start": 839.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That illustrates", "start": 843.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that with golf,", "start": 846.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as with flutes,", "start": 849.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's hard to decide the question", "start": 851.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of what justice requires,", "start": 854.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "without grappling with the question,", "start": 857.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"What is the essential nature", "start": 859.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the activity in question,", "start": 861.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and what qualities,", "start": 863.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what excellences", "start": 866.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "connected with that activity,", "start": 868.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are worthy of honor and recognition?\"", "start": 870.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let's take a final example", "start": 874.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's prominent in contemporary political debate:", "start": 876.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "same-sex marriage.", "start": 879.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are those who favor state recognition", "start": 883.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "only of traditional marriage", "start": 886.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between one man and one woman,", "start": 888.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and there are those who favor state recognition", "start": 891.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of same-sex marriage.", "start": 893.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How many here", "start": 895.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "favor the first policy:", "start": 897.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the state should recognize traditional marriage only?", "start": 899.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And how many favor the second, same-sex marriage?", "start": 904.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, put it this way:", "start": 908.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What ways of thinking", "start": 911.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about justice and morality", "start": 913.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "underlie the arguments we have", "start": 915.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "over marriage?", "start": 917.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The opponents of same-sex marriage say", "start": 919.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the purpose of marriage,", "start": 922.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "fundamentally, is procreation,", "start": 924.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that's what's worthy of honoring", "start": 926.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and recognizing and encouraging.", "start": 928.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the defenders of same-sex marriage say no,", "start": 931.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "procreation is not the only purpose of marriage;", "start": 934.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what about a lifelong, mutual, loving commitment?", "start": 938.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's really what marriage is about.", "start": 941.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So with flutes, with golf carts,", "start": 945.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and even with a fiercely contested question", "start": 948.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like same-sex marriage,", "start": 951.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Aristotle has a point.", "start": 954.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Very hard to argue about justice", "start": 957.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "without first arguing", "start": 959.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about the purpose of social institutions", "start": 962.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and about what qualities are worthy", "start": 965.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of honor and recognition.", "start": 967.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So let's step back from these cases", "start": 970.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and see how they shed light", "start": 973.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on the way we might improve, elevate,", "start": 976.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the terms of political discourse", "start": 979.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the United States,", "start": 982.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and for that matter, around the world.", "start": 984.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There is a tendency to think", "start": 987.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that if we engage too directly", "start": 989.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with moral questions in politics,", "start": 992.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's a recipe for disagreement,", "start": 994.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and for that matter, a recipe for", "start": 996.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "intolerance and coercion.", "start": 998.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So better to shy away from,", "start": 1000.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to ignore,", "start": 1002.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the moral and the religious convictions", "start": 1004.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that people bring to civic life.", "start": 1006.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It seems to me that our discussion", "start": 1008.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "reflects the opposite,", "start": 1011.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that a better way", "start": 1013.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to mutual respect", "start": 1016.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is to engage directly", "start": 1018.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the moral convictions", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "citizens bring to public life,", "start": 1022.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "rather than to require", "start": 1025.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that people leave their deepest moral convictions", "start": 1027.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "outside politics", "start": 1030.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "before they enter.", "start": 1032.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That, it seems to me, is a way", "start": 1034.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to begin to restore", "start": 1036.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the art of democratic argument.", "start": 1038.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 1040.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1042.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1045.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1047.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1050.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1052.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 1054.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thanks. Thank you.", "start": 1056.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Chris.", "start": 1059.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thanks, Chris.", "start": 1061.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Chris Anderson: From flutes to golf courses", "start": 1064.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to same-sex marriage --", "start": 1066.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that was a genius link.", "start": 1068.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now look, you're a pioneer of open education.", "start": 1070.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Your lecture series was one of the first to do it big.", "start": 1073.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What's your vision for the next phase of this?", "start": 1075.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: Well, I think that it is possible.", "start": 1078.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the classroom, we have arguments", "start": 1081.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on some of the most fiercely held", "start": 1084.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "moral convictions that students have", "start": 1087.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about big public questions.", "start": 1089.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I think we can do that in public life more generally.", "start": 1091.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And so my real dream would be", "start": 1094.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to take the public television series", "start": 1096.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that we've created of the course --", "start": 1098.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's available now, online,", "start": 1100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "free for everyone anywhere in the world --", "start": 1102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to see whether we can partner with institutions,", "start": 1104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "at universities in China, in India,", "start": 1107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Africa, around the world,", "start": 1109.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to try to promote", "start": 1111.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "civic education", "start": 1114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and also a richer kind", "start": 1116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of democratic debate.", "start": 1118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "CA: So you picture, at some point,", "start": 1121.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "live, in real time,", "start": 1123.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you could have this kind of conversation, inviting questions,", "start": 1125.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but with people from China and India joining in?", "start": 1128.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "MS: Right. We did a little bit of it here", "start": 1131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with 1,500 people in Long Beach,", "start": 1133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we do it in a classroom at Harvard", "start": 1135.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with about 1,000 students.", "start": 1138.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Wouldn't it be interesting", "start": 1140.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to take this way", "start": 1142.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of thinking and arguing,", "start": 1145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "engaging seriously with big moral questions,", "start": 1147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "exploring cultural differences", "start": 1150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and connect through a live video hookup,", "start": 1152.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "students in Beijing and Mumbai", "start": 1156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and in Cambridge, Massachusetts", "start": 1158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and create a global classroom.", "start": 1160.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's what I would love to do.", "start": 1162.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1164.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "CA: So, I would imagine", "start": 1168.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that there are a lot of people who would love to join you in that endeavor.", "start": 1170.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Michael Sandel. Thank you so much. (MS: Thanks so much.)", "start": 1173.26, "duration": 2.0}]